  "prompt": "Where does the word \"suicide\" come from?",
  "response": "The word \"suicide\" originates from the New Latin term \"suicidium,\" which literally means \"the act of killing oneself.\" It is a compound of two Latin words: \"sui,\" meaning \"of oneself,\" and \"cidium,\" meaning \"killing\" or \"slaying\" (from \"caedere,\" to kill). The term was introduced into the English language in the 17th century. The first known use of the word in English is often attributed to Sir Thomas Browne in his work \"Religio Medici,\" written in 1642. The term was initially used to describe the act of self-killing in a neutral or descriptive sense, though it has since acquired more complex and often heavily stigmatized connotations.",
